<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4B/603</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Japanese Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Saito</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 250</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-29">December 29, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor, under instructions from
                            my Government, to communicate to you the following:—</p>
                        <p>In accordance with Article XXIII of the Treaty concerning the Limitation
                            of Naval Armament, signed at Washington on the 6th February, 1922, the
                            Government of Japan hereby give notice to the Government of the United
                            States of America of their intention to terminate the said Treaty, which
                            will accordingly cease to be in force after the 31st December, 1936.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Saito</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>